<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870717-0053 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Home Shopping Network Inc.</HL><DD> 07/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HSN </IN><TEXT>   Home Shopping Network Inc. expects to report fiscal fourth-quarter net income &quot;in the range of $7 million to $8 million,&quot; depressed by efforts to win back customers lost because of telephone problems, said Roy Speer, chairman and chief executive officer. The Clearwater, Fla.-based video-retailing company, however, expects to report an approximate 4.2% revenue rise to $160 million in the quarter ending Aug. 31 compared with the third period, Mr. Speer said. In the year-ago fourth quarter, the fast growing company had net of $5.6 million on sales of $53.4 million. In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange yesterday, Home Shopping closed at $16.875 a share, down 87.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>